confirmed 0, deaths 0, recovered 0  Wanlov on set  Ghanaian musician Wanlov the Kubulor drops a brand new one titled “PPP”, featuring M3NSA and Mind You. “PPP” is an abbreviation for politicians, police, and pastors, and the rapper and singer goes hard on the three groups of people on this socially conscious song. According to Wanlov: “Corona is here. Politicians are using the relief loans to feed only themselves & party members. Police are slapping hungry citizens & not washing their hands before or after. Pastors are waiting for covid19 to go so they can perform their miracles again.” Watch the video, and download the tune below.  See also: Wanlov the Kubolor ft. Sena Dagadu – The Once   The post VIDEO: Wanlov the Kubolor ft. M3NSA & Mind You – PPP appeared first on Latest Naija Nigerian Music, Songs & Video – Notjustok. Source: NotJust okay Check your inbox or spam folder to confirm your subscription. 